title.translation: Enforce Driver Shift Durations in Matching

description.translation: Match rides to drivers only if the rides can be completed within drivers current shifts. Set the value to 0 minutes to enforce the actual shift end time, a value greater than zero to add a positive buffer, and a negative value to add a negative buffer, effectively shortening and lengthening shift durations respectively. Disable the setting by leaving the value blank.
Set the maximum break duration. Once this time is reached, the break will end automatically.
Set the amount of time after which a driver can start another break
Define the area of operation with one or more polygons.
Choose whether to display the operational territory in the driver app or highlight the excluded areas.

title.translation: Cluster Nearby Vehicles in Driver App

description.translation: Display vehicles that are in a close proximity to one another as clusters in the Autofleet Driver App.
Set custom text that will be pre-populated in the Driver App SMS field when drivers initiate a text message to the contact person of the current stop point.

Set the state to which drivers will transition when they are activated to a vehicle. For operations that don't use the Autofleet Driver App, set the value to "Driving". If vehicle locking is triggered from the Autofleet Driver App, set the value to "Activating" or "Driver on the way", but not "Driving".
Set the amount of time ride assignment offers remain valid for driver with a manual assignment strategy. Note that long expiry times may have a negative impact on customer experience.
Set the amount of drivers that can be offered a ride at one time.
Reoptimize dispatched rides
Set the ETA below which rides will not be reoptimized. For example, if set to 3 min, a vehicle 2.5 minutes away from the pickup will not be reoptimized.

Only reoptimize the ride if the difference between the current vehicle ETA and the alternative vehicle ETA is above this value. Use this setting to reoptimize rides only if they provide a significant benefit. For example, reoptimize rides only if the ETA improvement is greater than 3 minutes from the current ETA.

Future rides will be considered for reoptimization if the start of the pickup window is below the set limit. This setting is only relevant if the the setting to dispatch future rides immediately is turned on.

Dispatch future rides upon creation rather than the default of dispatching future rides at the start of pickup windows. Future rides with pickup windows starting in the next 24 hours will be dispatched.

title.translation: EV Charging - Deactivate driver upon arrival

description.translation: Set if drivers should be deactivated from vehicles upon arriving to Fuel stop points for electric vehicles. Turn on if drivers are expected to leave vehicles while they are being charged.
Prevent client last names from being visible in the Driver App and ride data.

title.translation: Ride Offer Information in Driver App
